==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Acceptilation
<hw>Ac*cep`ti*la"tion</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>acceptilatio</ets> entry of a debt collected, acquittance, fr. p.
p. of <ets>accipere</ets> (cf. <er>Accept</er>) + <ets>latio</ets> a
carrying, fr. <ets>latus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>ferre</ets> to carry: cf.
F. <ets>acceptilation</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Civil Law)</fld>
<def>Gratuitous discharge; a release from debt or obligation without
payment; free remission.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Acception</ent>⟦br⟧
